        },
        {
          "target": "right",
          "name": "announcements",
          "headerText": "Nyheter i Hajk",
          "icon": "announcement",
          "text": "This release includes _[205 commits](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/compare/v4.1.0...v4.2.0) and changes across 173 files since Hajk 4.1. Packaged by @Hallbergs and @jacobwod, with contributions from the community. See the commit list for all contributors._\n\n## Summary\n\nHajk 4.2 combines stabilization efforts following the 4.0 update with a suite of new features and optimizations.\n\nFor an overview of planned development, refer to the [project roadmap](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/blob/master/ROADMAP.md).\n\nScroll down for a comprehensive list of changes! 🚀\n\n---\n\n## Changelog highlights\n\nFor a complete list of changes, see the [project changelog](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md).\n\nFor a full list of commits, visit [this link](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/compare/v4.1.0...v4.2.0-rc.1).\n\n### Added\n\n- Support for **cookie-less Matomo tracking**. [PR#1691](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1691)\n- **OpenStreetMap** is now a selectable **default background layer** in map config. See [commit](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/commit/e1b5f59c69b8985a498efee27aa76ea11ca4afbb) and [commit](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/commit/4040c7c11367620040efc7609a56e1b3b436cc67). Admin UI option added in [commit](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/commit/06c52b0cd863022f7c9a58e5103168627ac41172).\n- Updated **default projection** (in `simpleMapConfig.json` and `map_1.json`) to **EPSG:3857**. This improves rendering for the new OpenStreetMap background. [commit](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/commit/6f5a5dc89a5c18d49f5af2d26353036d35945b82)\n\n### Changed\n\n- **FmeServer plugin:** Select Tool now supports multi-feature selection/deselection. [PR#1708](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1708)\n- Upgraded Material UI (MUI) to v7. [PR#1658](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1658)\n- **OpenStreetMap**, white, and black backgrounds are now standard layers in LayerSwitcher, allowing visibility initialization via configuration. [PR#1680](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1680)\n- Replaced legacy `react-smooth-dnd` with `dnd-kit`. [PR#1689](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1689)\n- Updated **Introduction module** for Hajk 4 compatibility, introducing two tour modes (Full and LayerSwitcher). [PR#1664](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1664)\n- Refactored the **Anchor tool** into a dialog component. [PR#1711](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1711)\n- QuickAccess: LayerGroups are now shown as breadcrumbs, with each group’s layers displayed beneath it. [PR#1726](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1726)\n\n### Fixed\n\n- **Bookmarks:** Corrected button state logic. [PR#1609](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1609)\n- **Bookmarks:** \"Add\" button is now conditionally enabled based on input presence. [PR#1657](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1657)\n- **WFS:** Resolved URL parsing inconsistencies that hindered layer loading from certain services. [PR#1677](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1677)\n- **DialogWindowPlugin:** Fixed toolbar button visibility issues during state toggling. [issue](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/issues/1687)\n- **LayerSwitcher:** Prevented duplicate legend graphics when a custom group legend is defined. [issue](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/issues/1644)\n- **LayerSwitcher:** Hidden Quick Access Presets when functionality is disabled in Admin. [PR](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1693)\n- **LayerSwitcher:** Standardized info buttons for groups to match regular/group layers (backward compatible). [PR](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/pull/1699)\n- **LayerSwitcher:** Enabled searching by LayerGroup name. GroupLayer search now expands to reveal sublayers. Closes [issue](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/issues/1722)\n- **Infoclick:** Fixed boolean value inversion occurring under specific database conditions. [issue](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/issues/1698)\n- **Client:** Added \"Access Denied\" UI feedback for 403 Backend responses. Closes [issue](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/issues/1705)\n\n### Security\n\n- Upgraded dependencies in Client and Backend. [commit](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/commit/2bee79696a66413749fb70c32b5c0b1cb7d4835f) and [commit](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/commit/6f8f1741cfba6cb7eb57bf65943a8af192af7bc2)\n\n---\n\n## Downloads\n\nHajk can be deployed using pre-built release packages or via Docker.\n\n### Pre-built packages\n\nThere are two versions of the downloadable package:\n\n- **Simple Edition:** Static files only (no backend/admin). Configuration relies on JSON files.\n- **NodeJS Edition:** Full stack, including Backend, Frontend, and Admin.\n\n1. [Hajk 4.2 NodeJS edition](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/releases/download/v4.2.0/hajk-v4.2.0-nodejs.zip)\n2. [Hajk 4.2 Simple edition](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/releases/download/v4.2.0/hajk-v4.2.0-simple.zip)\n\n### Docker container\n\nThe container is available on Docker Hub: [hallbergs/hajk](https://hub.docker.com/r/hallbergs/hajk).\n\n---\n\n## Installation\n\nRefer to the [installation guide](https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/wiki/Installation-guide-%28for-pre-packaged-releases%29).\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/hajkmap/Hajk/compare/v4.1.0...v4.2.0",
